Software Development Plan
1) Introduction
Forum ResetEra is a popular discussion platform for people to post questions, ideas, and thoughts for
popular video games. Not only it helps users review unique game features, but also engages them in the
discussion of developing their own games. Available in an assortment of enthusiastic journaling and
development of game-related articles. The forum is available through web browser connection, accessible
at all hours of the day and night, promising a ninety-nine percent uptime.
The goal of the project is to capture and store key information from the ResetEra Discussion forums to
learn about its feature and content. By applying a search algorithm, we examine all redirect hyperlinks that
are included in the forum markup file. From here, a list of redirects is generated ready to be stored in the
database library to enable information retrieval when needed. Ultimately, the objective of the project is to
arrange the most frequently used site vocabulary into text cloud images that best represent the RestEra
forum.
The purpose of this software development plan is to set forth the managerial process in terms of project
milestones, stakeholder communication, and resource utilization. Appropriately document application
design and software architecture to best address program functionality. Eventually, providing sufficient
guidance to developers by referencing specific standards, tools, and resources associated with the
development process.
a) Purpose
The purpose of the proposed software development plan is to establish documented procedures for
managing the engineering processes related to the web crawler application. The goal is to prepare the
project architect for archiving a high-quality production process in tasks related to collecting, prioritizing,
and collaborating activities.
b) Scope
Based on established managerial activities, the scope of the project is to align the ResetEra discussion
forum with engineering requirement specifications. Initiates data management on the site contents into
the development of web crawler applications. The goal is to bring working code meeting project
requirements with the highest quality given current constraints and capability. With project source code
provided by stakeholders, the project team is responsible for code learning, adjustment, and integration.
Tasks involved include:
1) Retrieve information from indicated ResetEra forum
2) Organize and store data in a structured manner
3) Establish function to find and retrieve key information
4) Generate report on discovered data from ResetEra forum

e) Overview
This document is intended to be a continuous process throughout web crawler application development
and integration. The process analyzes site information, prioritizes task activities, as well as assigns
collaboration roles and responsibilities. Establishing shared understanding among projects by controlling
all aspects of change, minimize risks that are involved in the engineering process. The following sections
cover the roles of involved stakeholders, project organization, managerial process, and risk assessment.
2) Project Overview
a) Project Purpose, Scope, and Objectives
The goal of the project is to develop a Web Crawler application to retrieve and organize information from
RestEra gaming discussion forums. The project team is expected to deliver all related managerial
documentation including team management, risk assessment, architecture design with an estimated
project completion time of 3 months.

b) Assumptions and Constraints
Assumptions
1) Major technology change will not be experienced during the course of development
2) Project member availability as described for the course of development
3) ResetEra forum will be hosted during the 3 month development time
4) Project solutions will not be hosted (resides on the local computer)
5) Project funding is not expected
6) No training needs to be conducted
Constraints
1) Limited time is available to complete the project
2) Limited skill and coding knowledge across the team member
3) Potential integration risks in ResetEra site build with our Web Crawler application

4) Management Process
a) Project Estimates
PERT Analysis
Program Evaluation and Review Technique is a method used to examine the tasks that are in a schedule
and determine a variation of the Critical Path Method. It analyzes the time required to complete each task
and its associated dependencies to determine the minimum time to complete a project. The three factors
are indicated as the following:
Optimistic: 45 days in the case of accelerated project flow
Most Likely: 60 days according to the planed detailed
Pessimistic: 70 days with the incomplete project and poor quality at the due date
The PERT analysis estimated the project completion time to be 59 days.

d) Project Monitoring and Control
i)Requirements Management Plan
Please refer to Requirement Management Plan enclosed in the portfolio.
ii)Schedule Control Plan
The project schedule is estimated based on planned project work activities and team member expertise,
derived from approved work breakdown structure as part of the planning effort. Dependency analysis is
conducted to determine tasks dependencies and the order of activities to be followed. For example, tasks
for architecture engineer and development engineer do not begin until week 4, members assigned with
engineer roles may choose to take a break to better prepare for upcoming tasks, or volunteer in assisting
management activities.
Project undergoes the process of monitoring and reporting on tasks progresses as well as controls such
that changes to the scheduled activities require team-wide approval for schedule adjustment. The
facilitator is responsible for generating a weekly schedule reporting on whether or not the team had been
stay on track for deliverables due by dates. If necessary, product quality may be reduced with fewer
features (crawlers with a reduced number of pages or withdrawal of limited information) for getting the
project back to schedule and control.
iii)Budget Control Plan
For the nature of this project, budget spending is mostly considered with human resources and the
number of man-hours. In practice, the team will regularly compare its progress with scheduled time and
expenses to identify whether or not corrective actions are needed. In the event of the project running
behind schedule, tasks may be re-distributed in a balanced order or identify alternative sources of funds.
iv)Quality Control Plan
The NextEra Web Crawler attempts to archive its designated quality by implementing quality management
strategies establishing integrated quality standards, quality measurement, and continuous monitoring to
bring the potent product. The quality planning process ensures team-wide knowledge sharing through
well-established communication, member identify and distributes tasks, procedures, and descriptions by
using Microsoft Teams. Weekly meetings are held to assess quality assurance, the team is to review the
project process, discrepancies, and findings that may be addressed before the upcoming deliverable. A
checklist method is used as an integral part of the quality review, whether or not respective requirements
were met within the indicated specification. As changes arise, these review meetings are appropriately
recorded, documented, and disseminated to teams.

e) Risk Management Plan
Risks are defined as events that have probabilities of occurring which may bring positive or negative
impacts on the project. We specifically address common risks that would affect project cost, schedule, and
performances in a negative way in the best effort to mitigate those risks.
Risks identified are:
1) Integration Risks - Highly likely to happen as we are working with unknown web structures on top
of provided code with minimum knowledge about. The project team is looking at preparing
external resources as backup and alternative solutions to recover integration risk.
2) Resource Risks - Due to lack of budget, free and open-source software were mostly selected,
these types of software may be subjected to lack of support and server downtime impacting the
development progress.
3) People Risks - Decrease or Reduction on availability of human resources due to external factors,
experiencing a shortage of people and lack of motivation is likely to alter
Risks response is prepared for all identified risks, these risks are distributed to team members for
evaluation in order to determine the best course of actions to better track and report emerging risks in a
timely manner.
f) Close-out Plan
The project team will go through rounds of validation processes ensuring the final product has met the
requirement of the documentation and stakeholders. A retrospective session is to be conducted to collect
feedback for improvements as well as identify lessons learned, contributing to supporting best practices
for future projects. Final rounds of project records, documentation, and artifacts are to be reviewed with
minor modifications to ensure documented accuracy and consistency. On the final deliverable, the project
team is disassembled.

Use Case Guideline
The NextEra Forum user requirements are seen as the capability to begin the data mining process, given
the ability to access the data mined from the site. Which may be obtaining a list of hyperlinks, post
content, and access to the database in keyword searching. Eventually, be able to download Word Cloud
images of the top 50 frequently appeared words that represent the forum.
iii) Software Architecture
The architecture refers to the fundamental structure of the system, the following diagram outlines the
blueprint of the NextEra Web Crawler application by providing abstraction and coordination mechanism
among integrated components.
iv) Architecture Diagram
Three components are presented in the NextEra Web Crawler application, a python section responsible for
fetching URL hyperlinks and content associated with these links; The database section responsible for
storing fetched data with queries to obtain parsing, count, and sorting results. Finally, the external web API
for generating Word Cloud images based on the obtained results.

vii) Application Deployment
The deployment is intended to ensure the delivery of successful service by detailing the components,
dependencies, and interactions with subsystems. The goal is to support application execution by
establishing a well-managed process on system flow. As shown in the following diagram, the presented
nodes are:
1) Client Device - Any computing system capable of running Python with a stable HTTP connection.
In this case, cookies and cache files may be used to track history for better execution flow
2) Application - The intelligent part of the system with logic and data management responsible for
connectivity, data organization, and query management
3) Database - Data storage component with MySQL to process structuralized information for content
regulation
4) Web Server - The NextEra forum hosting web content to be crawled from
5) Web API - The third-party engine for generating Word Cloud image for given text input
Connections required are defined as:
1) HTTP - the communication methodology that uses TCP and UDP protocol to establish a channel
between the client device and web server for content access and download
2) JDBC/ODBC - the MySQL application programming interface to access and alter database content

6) Supporting Process Plans
a) Configuration Management Plan
With proper configuration management, we aim to accurately identify and manage project deliverables
including monitoring, tracking, controlling associated processes throughout the development cycle.
Project tasks are distributed to team members according to their expertise as described in section 3.
adopting a decentralized self-manage structure, all members are expected to continuously monitor and
inspect high-level measurement for process improvement. The anticipated size of the project output is
estimated to be 5 MB in PNG format accessible for download through the BlackBoard submission site.
Project-related documentation are named according to the functionality and purpose of the artifact. The
name formatting follows the structure as indicated:
PROJECT IDENTIFICATION_TEAM NAME_ARTIFACT_VERSION
Microsoft Teams is used as the primary communication channel and workspace repository for file sharing
and simultaneous edits for design artifacts. Adopting periodic progress reports and the weekly team
meets, any issues identified during the development are closely monitored by all team members. Change
requests may be proposed through Microsoft Teams for team-wide review, proceeded upon approval of all
team members.
b) Evaluation Plan
This section describes how we monitor and evaluate our software, clarifying the important
decision-making points and information that stakeholders are concerned about. Considering indicators
evaluated from the perspective of the stakeholders and user. The specified criteria and standards should
meet the quality expectation including information validity, user control, program reliability, language
consistency, and application availability. These elements are independently rated among stakeholders
(team members) in the construction of summary scores. If an average score from a particular criterion is
rated as unsatisfactory, a change request may be proposed to refine the indicated criteria.
1) Documentations are clear, concise, and informative to intended audiences
2) The language is consistent worded free from spelling and grammatical errors
3) All subjects related to the development are covered in a comprehensive manner
4) Proper communication has been established throughout the development process
5) Requirements are clearly interpreted by the stakeholders
6) The application supports the needs of the stakeholder
7) The system is error-free and reliable for normal use

Requirements Management Plan
1. Introduction
Forum ResetEra is a popular discussion platform for people to post questions, ideas, and thoughts for
popular video games. Not only it helps users review unique game features, but also engages them in the
discussion of developing their own games. Available in an assortment of enthusiastic journaling and
development of game-related articles. The forum is available through web browser connection, accessible
at all hours of the day and night, promising a ninety-nine percent uptime.
The goal of the project is to capture and store key information from the ResetEra Discussion forums to
learn about its feature and content. By applying a search algorithm, we examine all redirect hyperlinks that
are included in the forum markup file. From here, a list of redirects is generated ready to be stored in the
database library to enable information retrieval when needed. Ultimately, the objective of the project is to
arrange the most frequently used site vocabulary into text cloud images that best represent the RestEra
forum.
The purpose of this requirements management plan is to set forth the plans and procedures for collecting
documenting, analyzing, and managing the project requirements. The term requirements refers to
qualities, capabilities, or conditions that must be present to satisfy a contractual obligation or other
formally imposed specification
1.1 Purpose
The purpose of the proposed requirement management plan is to establish documented procedures for
managing the engineering processes related to the web crawler application. A set of techniques are
prepared for documenting, analyzing, and agreeing on development towards software requirements. The
goal is to set up planning for a high-quality production process, ensuring product development goals are
successfully met.
1.2 Scope
Based on established managerial activities, the scope of the project is to align the ResetEra discussion
forum with engineering requirement specifications. Initiates data management on the site contents into
the development of web crawler applications. The goal is to bring working code meeting project
requirements with the highest quality given current constrain and capability. With project source code
provided by stakeholders, the project team is responsible for code learning, adjustment, and integration.
Tasks involved include:
1) Retrieve information from indicated ResetEra forum
2) Organize and store data in a structured manner
3) Establish function on find and retrieve key information
4) Generate report on discovered data from ResetEra forum

3.2 Traceability
By definition, traceability is the ability to verify the history, location, and item dependency for recorded
identification. Basically, given the ability for us to keep track of requirements and identify verifiable
entities associated with each requirement.
3.2.1 Criteria for <traceability item>
Traceability helps us identify the origin of a given requirement, the use of a traceability matrix is adapted
to correlate the many-to-many relationship to validate relationship completeness. With criteria gathered
from stakeholder needs, desired features, use cases, and involved actors. The traceability matrix maps and
traces user requirements with test cases such that one feature must be mapped to one need. However,
every use case may map one or more scenarios and features, as one-to-many relationships needs exist in
our design. The goal of our traceability design is to fulfill all requirements, needs requested by
stakeholders and verify the application is capable to implement the feature requested.

1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
The purpose of the requirement specification is to establish documented procedures for managing the
proposed stakeholder requirements. It is used to distribute critical information among project team
members in terms of operation, quality, and communication to keep everyone on the same page. The use
of this document helps ensure requirements are been fulfilled by providing in-depth descriptions of the
software that will be developed.
1.2 Scope
This document is intended to outline the requirements and scope for the NextEra Web Crawler project.
The goal of the project is to capture and store key information from the ResetEra Discussion forums to
learn about its feature and content. By applying a search algorithm, embedded hyperlinks are examined
to enable information retrieval when needed. Ultimately, the objective of the project is to arrange the
most frequently used site vocabulary into text cloud images that best represent the RestEra forum.

1.5 Overview
This document is intended to collect and categorize imposed requirements regards to system design and
verification. Specifies the system component including its functional and non-functional units such as
interface, usability, reliability, and standards captured through stakeholder analysis. Followed by legal and
copyright standards to maintain requirement validity.
2. Overall Description
Product Feature & User Description
This system utilizes data mining technology based on the Python language allowing imports from HTML
markup files for content extraction. The system consists of two parts, a python script for file execution
and an SQL database for data management. The user classes system targets are labeled as follows:
Role
Description
System Operator
The engineering team responsible for code maintenance and execution
Data Operation
Internal member for data organization and maintenance with appropriate
access privilege
Public Users
The primary user of the system who would like to extract data in text-cloud
formatting
Environment & Constraints
The rule for selecting hardware and software resources are based on cost and functionality. Window 10 is
chosen as the operating system with hardware spec Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-8700K CPU @ 3.70GHz to
operate needed software applications including Web Browser, SQL database server, and Python. The data
management portion of the storage environment sets privileged access based on user role, where
engineering members are given admin control with the rest provided with commit rights. Based on our
adopted environment, technical constraints are listed below:
1) The probability of Python application code not running on another operating system
2) The database may not be accessible for the end-user environment
3) The end-user computing environment may or may not handle our data processing rate
User Documentation
User documentation is provided including tutorials, help pages, and a complete user manual. The tutorial
will provide a step-by-step process to use the application with instructions on environment setup included
in the user manual. Including the overview of system features, architectures, sample screenshots, and
usage instructions.

3. Specific Requirements
3.1 Functionality
The system consists of a python script and the database works by extracting data from HTML files,
capturing the hyperlinks, and data-mine contents from the site to be stored on an SQL database server.
Queries are constructed on the server end by sorting and categorizing captured data into related terms
and frequency vocabulary are used on the site. The top 50 most frequently used vocabs are selected to be
interfaces with a web portal in order to construct a word-cloud image that best represents NextEra
Forum.
The goal is to construct high-performing software pieces to effectively complete the indicated tasks in an
automated manner. The project team will elicit user requirements across use cases, stakeholder needs,
and system indications to describe the expected use and functionality of the system. As described in
Requirement Management Plan included in the project portfolio, sets of activities including conferencing,
review, and pre-validation sessions are held to provide a comprehensive description of user requirements.
The following sections described the refined list of the feasible requirements that accurately represent
the user and system to be used on the implementation. Note: Traceable Item may be referred to
Requirement Management Plan for item originated in terms of traceability.

3.8.2 Hardware Interfaces
The application requires the installation of Python to be the execution platform. Therefore, the

3.8.4 Communications Interfaces
The system communicates SQL database through JDBC connection and internet with HTTP. Therefore,
requiring network service to interact with web servers with TCP/IP network protocol.
3.9 Licensing Requirements
No licensing requirements are imposed with the utilization of open-sourced software applications. The
legal contract of selected software applications declares these software can be used in commercial
applications.
4. Supporting Information
User manuals are included within the project portfolio to increase the understandability of the system
design, architecture, and deployment. Please refer to User Manual and Software Development Plan for
supporting information.
